TY  - JOUR
TI  - Threats, Counter-Threats, and Strategic Voting
AU  - Pattanaik, Prasanta K.
AB  - [This paper seeks to prove that under a large class of group decision rules some sincere voting situations will be unstable because of strategic manipulation by single individuals. The concept of stability used is weaker than the stability concepts figuring in many earlier contributions in this area, insofar as under the concept used here any individual, while disrupting a given voting situation, considers the possibility of retaliation by other individuals.]
C1  - Full publication date: Jan., 1976
